< Text>
I recently bought a 2018 Kia Soul + from Elk Grove Buick GMC in Elk Grove, California. I had been anticipating purchasing it since before Christmas, but am the sole caregiver of my disabled sister and finding the time to buy a car was difficult. When I looked again for that specific car after Christmas, I couldn't find the vehicle and figured it had been sold. I was shopping specifically for Kia Soul + cars because they are so good. When I looked a couple of weeks ago, the car reappeared in the car search sites. I kept my eye on it again, and then noticed the price had dropped another $600. That's when I called and spoke with Nabil. He was very courteous and promptly obtained what the total cost of the car would be from the manager. There were a couple of points that I wanted to haggle on, and he was right there to help the entire process. I am a difficult customer because I'm very firm on what I will pay. Nabil was great in that he would go back and forth between the manager and me to get me my deal. When I finally came to purchase the car, it took a while as usual to complete all of the paperwork. In the meantime, my sister was waiting patiently for me in the van that we use for her wheelchair. Nabil was very kind and actually went out to talk with her while I was filling out the forms. He let her know I wouldn't be too much longer and was reassuring. After completing the paperwork and walking out to leave, they were kind enough to let me park the van overnight while I drove my sister home in the new car. I came back the next day with my brother's help to retrieve the van. I purchased five different flavors of cookies, a dozen each, and some favorite lemon almond candies for him. I told him he could share or take them home for himself. Of course, his kindness couldn't let him take them all for himself and he told me everyone enjoyed them as well as he did. I told him his new slogan should be: If you want a great deal, ask for Nabil.
He's truly one in a milion.

Gale J< /Text>

Beware!!! Found a used Charger I was interested in online from this Dealership. Went back and fourth over price with the salesperson who kept quoting me higher than what the online price was listed for. When he finally agreed to honor the online price and sent me a full cost breakdown with taxes, fees, etc. there was an $895 fee for Etch/Shield. Most Dealers charge around $300-$400 for window etching which is still a rip-off. When I told them I wouldn't pay that much for Etching the sales manager told me it couldn't be removed and they had to charge the full price for it. The cost to do this service is usually less than $50 BTW! I walked away from the deal. Not so much because of the price, but because any dealership that is shady enough to impose such an overpriced "scam" is untrustworthy and not worthy of my business. Shame too, I really liked the car and definitely would have purchased it otherwise.</text>

< review>
Bought a vehicle from them in September. Everything was pretty good through the purchase/financing process. In fact, I was able to get approved for a loan when others couldn't do it. However, I opted for the extended warranty plan and GAP coverage, which by the way is optional, you are not required to purchase it. About a week after I purchased the vehicle I decided I wanted to cancel the warranty and GAP coverage and have the nearly $4,000 total refunded and a check mailed to the finance company. I was told I had to come in to sign some forms needed to cancel those coverages. I explained it's over a two hour drive to come just to sign a form to get these optional plans cancelled and be refunded for it .They said they would mail the forms, but I doubt they will because when I email them I don't even get responses until I send a follow up email. It's coming close to the 60 days that they allow for a full refund, and I'm concerned they are going to try to no refund the entire amount. It's been a complete nightmare dealing with this. I recommend that you really look at what you are getting in the optional coverages. Also, if you want GAP check with your insurance company to see what they offer first. If you these optional plans you may never be able to cancel them and get a refund!</review>

< Review>
I keep forgetting to post my review. I have been checking out different nail salons in the Lodi area but had not found any I really liked. When I went to VIP NAILS & SPA, I was immediately impressed. I believe her name was Bella, she was so sweet. She even gave my advice for wedding planning. Overall I left satisfied. Within a week almost all my nails were chipped, obviously I was bummed, but when I called to schedule a time to come in I wasn't met with push back. When I arrived, it was decided that the whole thing needed to be redone. It was so refreshing to get great customer service, as it past places I have been blamed for the polish chipping. They had just gotten new machines, which is why my no-chip chipped so quick. my new no chip manicure lasted more than 3 weeks. I already made another appointment before I go on a trip. I definitely recommend this place!</Review>

A few months ago we did Chung Ki Wa in K-Town and - to my way of eating - this place was better. My family first went here around five months ago and and thought it was good. We've visited 3 times since then and been increasingly disappointed each visit.  At first it was just that it was hard to get a server to bring you more water, then bringing the wrong food and the sushi on top of the rolls seemed to be getting smaller and smaller then on our last visit we were served some brown salmon that was an odd texture. Our thinking was that the sushi chef made this roll, they must have seen how off the fish was but they served it to us anyhow. The manager came by and after we explained she said ok and took it away, there was no I'm so sorry about that or this isn't standard. That same night we sat and waited and waited for our check. We love sushi and we don't mind spending money on it but when you get the bill and the food was disappointing it always feels like a rip off. While we were eating still they began cleaning the floor with some really strong chemicals which is sort of gross while you're eating. We will not be giving this place another chance. The place is far from being updated but I dont really care how a place looks if it clean and the food is good. Poor service, comically small sushi on top of rolls and bad fish, that's a bad combo.</review>

< Review>
First off let me say there people are great, friendly, and knowledgeable. Let me just explain why this place is not for me and do not let it deter you from coming here. First we got the wife's car done here for a replacement thermostat, which now runs fine. They got the job done but also added charges for inspecting clamps and hoses, a quite large charge I may add, for parts you are already looking at and working with. They also added for draining coolant and refilling which you must do when replacing a thermostat, as it begins to drain when you undo the clamps.

For my car it was simply my brakes pads and rotors which would have ran me $300 dollars at this shop. Also a new wheel they "couldnt" find except for $200 from the manufacturer, but I got a new one for $70 at a wheel dealership. That job was around $370 at the shop even though the wheels are off while replacing the rotors. All in all I spent $150 and 45minutes of my time doing what would have cost me approx $700 at this shop.

Again these are great people only doing their job and they need to make a profit, but just to too much of an extent for me to come back, they will get the job done but not for me.< /Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< Text>
Dr. B looks out for your pet AND your wallet. He is very knowledgeable and thankfully, empathetic. ( Is that the right word for it?) I know he has the pet in the mind as well as the owner. He always offers an alternative treatment method or gives you advice on what to do at home if you cannot afford to get all your treatment at the clinic. Their prices are very reasonable and the staff is nice. The facility is a little worn, but I find it warm and inviting.

My favorite part about this place is the groomer, Ann. She uses all-natural shampoos and conditioners, no chemicals and pesticides. I know my dogs are in good hands when they go to her- she takes her time to groom each animal and gives them a little bandana when she's done.</Text>

< date>
1604559495330</date>
< Review>
I will be brutally honest; I came here to give a a highly negative review giving onlyt 2 to 3 stars to this business. Here is why. The negative first then the why I still am giving this small shop 5 stars.
I went in about a week ago and purchased two Gourami's and a betta. I noticed on the way home, one of them was acting funny. I got home and looked into the plastic bag and notice orange setting at the bottom. First impression was they ate something orange. Then after 2day in the tank I noticed the fins started disappearing. I then isolated the fish and by the next (3rd) day, he was dead. Tail almost gone, dorsal fin was going next. The second Gourami also looked really sick. Then eventually was just laying on the bottom of the tank barely breathing. Which was when I made the call to the store. They told me they'd replace the fish.  I take them both in and right away check the tank at the store they both came out of; sure enough, several others in that tank had torn up fins. I believe that tank had a disease in it called fin rot.
Now for the positive. They didn't really question me because you could see it was obvious on the fish. They immediately helped me, the guys there are very helpful and generous, making sure I knew they were there for any questions I may have. I ended up picking up black neon tetras ( they're awesome). One thing I appreciate the most is good customer service. The sense of knowing someone is willing to help and even share their experiences.
Now, a little more bad news. I get the tetras home. These were going in my 5 gal planted taking with the Betta I had purchased with the Gourami's. I acclimate them and release them in the tank, give them a little food and look in the tank which is when I noticed the betta had ick. This tank has been empty for a month and the betta was the first fish to go in this tank by itself. Which tells me he was sold to me with the disease.
My advise to the business. Please go through your tanks and treat them for these diseases. My first 3 fish purchased there were diseased. I'm just hoping now that the tetras are healthy.< /Review>

<Time>1499393534788</Time><rating>3<//rating>< text>
Let me start off by first saying that I have been going to this nail place for about 10 years now and although I have tried to find another nail salon in my area I still have not found anything that is as clean as this salon. They use sterilized instruments which I really appreciate and they do very good work the quality is excellent the prices can be a little bit High so don't think you're coming in to spend no $35 to $40. The only thing I have a problem with is that when you go to a nail salon you kind of want to get a little peace and quiet away from the home, away from the kids away, from the husband but you can't because they are talking so loud all of the nail technicians in a different language that you can't understand so at times you can feel like they could be talking about you. I know this goes on in every single salon I've ever been too but it's very annoying when they are so loud.  At least if you're going to gossip and talk about things speak in a language that we can all understand because I feel it's very rude and disrespectful.  Just today I was I was getting my pedicure the lady asked me to touch the water and it was very hot steaming hot I put my foot in and I burnt it when I told her it was hot she talked to the other lady in her language like if I was lying about the water the water was so hot I felt like they were trying to cook my feet.  As I was getting my full set done as well my nail lady answered her phone 4 different times as well as got up on two different occasions one to wax someone's eyebrows and the other time to go buy some food or something from out front which is okay but if I'm going to be spending that much money I expect to get full attention. But like I said I've been going there for years have not found any Salon better and they do really good work.< /text>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
I am very pleased to have engage KPB immigration law firm on April 2020 for their help with my naturalization application for U.S. citizenship.    It was after months of endless search for a immigration law firm who is willing to undertake my case.    The search experience was stressful.  I contacted Van Der Hout LLP, spoke to one of the associate, who thereafter did not respond to my email on how to proceed.    I also contacted Fragoman immigration law firm which helped me to apply for my green card in year 2015.    One of the senior partners responded my email and agreed to undertake my case.   I was asked to upload all my personal information on Fragoman case portal.   After doing so, I patiently waited for respond.  Week after week I followed up with calls and emails and yet there was no respond.   I was extremely frustrated for being kept in the dark for over a month.
I restarted the search on google and came across KPB.     Wilson Purves who is one of the partners took my call and has then personally attended to the whole application process.   My case is actually not complicating!  Wilson and his assistant Valeria are great.    They were attentive and timely in helping me to put together all the required documentation and completed the application forms.  Great team work!    KPB is genuine in wanting to help people cause they truly understand the emotional insights.
My application has been submitted to U.S. Immigration department in May 2020 and is a waiting process now.

Thank you Wilson and Valeria.   I highly recommend KPB .

Ann
July 2020<//Review>

<Gmap_id>0x80858086275a2801:0xa6593cc4d435412e< /Gmap_id>< Review>
My cousin found and connected me up with Christopher, his assistant Hisae, and his team at Kerosky, Purves & Bogue LLP. After a rough interaction with my previous lawyer, the world of law and laywers left a severely bitter taste in my mouth and made me very distrustful and wary. However, after the initial meeting and consultation with Christopher, I had absolutely no doubt that I was in safe hands and I had absolutely nothing to worry about. They have offices throughout California but I dealt primarily with the San Francisco and Santa Rosa office.

Both Christopher and Hisae reply to their e-mails and phone calls remarkably fast, and they will explain everything down to the last detail for you. They will walk you through your situation, give you the options, and assist you through them. I had never left an appointment without my questions answered thoroughly, and I ALWAYS left feeling reassured, relaxed, and confident.

I worked directly hand-in-hand with Christopher and his team for a better part of 7-8 years (2009-2017) in regards to my immigration case, and I honestly cannot thank them enough for everything that they've done. Their work ethic and knowledge on all things immigration is remarkable, but most importantly I knew that they had my back no matter what happens. They treat you like family, they check-up on you like family, and they reassure you like family. In all honestly, they are the ONLY law group I recommend to anyone who has any immigration questions or concerns. I do not and will not trust any other law group other than Kerosky, Purves & Bogue.

If you have any immigration issues, I STRONGLY urge you to call or e-mail them. They ARE your advocate, and they truly do care about what happens to you.

Because of Christopher and his team, I no longer have to be afraid and can finally come out of the shadows after so long. They thoroughly relieved me and my husband's worries, and I am forever indebted to the folks at Kerosky, Purves & Bogue.

Thank you, Christopher and team, times a billon. Thank you for coming into our lives and becoming a part of our family, and thank you for all that you have done for me. We cannot thank you guys enough!!<//Review>
